The Ukraine Flag is a pro that would be used post-war, as it allows our modern audiences to understand the setting and geographical locstion of this preformance. Abandoning Family

Abdndoning Family is a key part of my version of the play, as it creates a modern take of losing relatives and loved ones. Linking this back to the original play, Anne Frank and her family would need to stay in hiding in order to stay alive, living off barely anything. Contrast to my play, people are losing family and having to go into hiding as well, but in the sense that if they don't, families will be split and killed. This creates a link between modern audiences and past histories of the war. This prop could also be in the kitchen table, with drawing of kids leaving their homes duing the war.

Loss Of Homes

Throughout the Ukraine war, Loss Of Homes has been an important subject, causing the innocent to become on the brink of homeless due to attacks on their country because of where they are from, an important prop that could be in use to reapresent homes and the destruction of them. To our present audience, this can be linked to themes such as exclusion, seperation, and purloin of their freedom, just like the original play portraying the same thing, but with a more narrow perspective, a choice I made so that our audiences can resonte with it more.

This solider would be an important prop, as it can realate to the loss of family for the good and protection of their country.
